        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-3595",
        "content": "It is supposed so at least;--and how it has come to pass, continued I, I know not; but they have certainly got the credit of understanding more of love, and making it better than any other nation upon earth; but, for my own part, I think them arrant bunglers, and in truth the worst set of marksmen that ever tried Cupid's patience.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-slow_e-normal",
